result.title: 2002 - 2002 Centre for Environment, Fisheries & Aquaculture Science (Cefas) English Channel Plankton Survey - RV Cirolana 2x/2002
result.name: 2002-2002-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-english-channel-plank-2002
result.notes:
Two plankton surveys were carried out (**RV Cirolana 2x/02: 29th April-12th 
May 2002** and RV Corystes 4z/03: 4th-9th May 2003) in the English Channel 
and southern North Sea to determine the distribution and abundance of crab
(*Cancer pagurus*) larvae in relation to fishing ground and sea bed sediments 
over the sea area bounded by latitudes 48° 30'N and 53° 00'N and longitudes 9° 
00'W and 2° 00'W. This data consists of the numbers and developmental stages 
of crab larvae, along with associated positional data and volumes filtered.
